From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [G4] `<|think_on|>` / `<|think_off|>` system-message thinking sentinels

Targets: templates/gemma4/upstream/<size>.jinja with **G1 already applied**
(Google's 2026-07-09 template). Applies to all five sizes.

**Stacks on G1.** G1 rewrites the `messages[0]['content'] is sequence` test,
which sits between the two lines G4 edits, so the two patches overlap in
context and cannot be applied in either order independently. G4 therefore
diffs against the G1-applied state. Apply order: **G1 -> G4 -> G8**
(all three verified clean on all five sizes). This is not a burden in
practice: the population that needs G4 (clients that cannot pass
`chat_template_kwargs`) is largely the same minijinja/LM Studio population
that needs G1, and G1 is byte-identical under jinja2 for normal inputs.

Status: OPT-IN. Gemma 4 ships no default `patched/` stack.

Failure mode: `enable_thinking` is only reachable as a template kwarg. A
client that cannot pass `chat_template_kwargs` (several OpenAI-compat front
ends, some LM Studio configurations) has no way to toggle Gemma 4's thinking
mode per request without rebuilding the request body or reloading the model.

Fix: scan the FIRST system/developer message for delimited sentinels and
override `enable_thinking`, then strip them from the rendered system text.
Google's 2026-07-09 rewrite normalizes the kwarg once
(`enable_thinking | default(false)`), so the override needs a single
injection point immediately after it.

  <|think_on|>   -> enable thinking
  <|think_off|>  -> disable thinking

Design (deliberately stronger than the Reddit prior art this derives from):

  1. **Delimited tokens, not bare words.** The prior art matches the bare
     substrings `ENABLE_THINKING` / `DISABLE_THINKING`, which fire on any
     literal occurrence — documentation, a quoted config line, a file path.
     That is exactly the P5 `/no_thinking` false-positive this repo already
     fixed once in R3 by moving to delimited tokens. G4 uses the same
     `<|think_on|>` / `<|think_off|>` spelling as Qwen's Q3.6-5, so the
     sentinel is identical across both families in this repo. The legacy
     bare words are deliberately NOT accepted.
  2. **split|join, never `.replace()`.** llama.cpp's minja silently drops
     the ENTIRE string when the replaced target sits at index 0, so a system
     prompt *starting* with a sentinel would erase the whole system block on
     C++ engines. The prior art uses `.replace()` twice and has this bug.
     (Same lesson as Q3.6-5 / froggeric v20.)
  4. **Both content forms.** The prior art guards on `content is string`, so
     a multimodal (sequence) system message is ignored. G4 handles both.
  5. **Rightmost-in-text wins** when both sentinels appear — an explicit
     per-request override appended to an inherited default beats the
     default. The prior art hard-codes "disable wins", which silently
     ignores position. (Same policy as Q3.6-5, itself an adversarial-review
     fix.)

Scope: sentinels are read only from the FIRST system/developer message, so a
sentinel appearing in user text or a tool response can never flip thinking
(prompt-injection guard, matching Q3.6-5's system-only scope).

Content-part safety: the scan mirrors the render exactly (per-part `trim` plus a
single space) so a sentinel cannot be synthesised across two text parts that
render apart, and both the scan and the strip tolerate a content part with no
`text` key (image/audio/video parts are legal in a system message; the earlier
revision crashed on them).

Verified under minja (`llama-template-analysis`, llama.cpp b9290) as well as
jinja2: byte-identical to the G1 state across 32 no-sentinel render combos
(all Gemma fixtures x {default, enable_thinking, preserve_thinking, tools}
plus multimodal and no-system conversations); sentinel enable/disable, kwarg
override, rightmost-wins in both orders, index-0 strip, sequence-form system
content, and user-message sentinels being ignored are each pinned by tests.

Small-variant note: E2B/E4B omit the non-thinking `<|channel>thought
<channel|>` bypass, so on those sizes the sentinel controls the `<|think|>`
system-turn injection and the post-tool-response thought channel only.

Prior art: u/No_Information9314, r/LocalLLaMA "Gemma 4 thinking system
prompt" (Apr 2026), snapshotted at
docs/sources/pastebins/W9VxRw09-no_information9314-gemma4-enable_thinking.jinja.
First shipped as a .patch 2026-07-20 (previously catalog-only).

--- a/templates/gemma4/upstream/26B-A4B-it.jinja
+++ b/templates/gemma4/upstream/26B-A4B-it.jinja
@@ -185,6 +185,35 @@
 {%- set loop_messages = messages -%}
 {%- set enable_thinking = enable_thinking | default(false) -%}
 {%- set preserve_thinking = preserve_thinking | default(false) -%}
+{#- G4: thinking-toggle sentinels. Scan the FIRST system/developer message for
+    `<|think_on|>` / `<|think_off|>` and override `enable_thinking`; the rightmost
+    occurrence wins. Sentinels take precedence over the kwarg and are stripped from
+    the rendered system text below.
+    minja-safe: llama.cpp's minja implements NO position-returning string method
+    (`rfind`/`find`/`index` are Undefined and abort the render), so rightmost-wins is
+    derived from `split` — whichever sentinel occurs LAST leaves the SHORTER trailing
+    segment, because the other's trailing segment must still contain it.
+    The scan mirrors the render exactly (per-part `trim` + single space) so a sentinel
+    cannot be synthesised across two text parts that render apart. -#}
+{%- set ns_g4 = namespace(sys_text='') -%}
+{%- if messages and messages[0]['role'] in ['system', 'developer'] -%}
+    {%- if messages[0]['content'] is string -%}
+        {%- set ns_g4.sys_text = messages[0]['content'] -%}
+    {%- elif messages[0]['content'] is iterable and messages[0]['content'] is not string and messages[0]['content'] is not mapping -%}
+        {%- for item in messages[0]['content'] -%}
+            {%- set ns_g4.sys_text = ns_g4.sys_text ~ ((item.get('text') or '') | trim) ~ ' ' -%}
+        {%- endfor -%}
+    {%- endif -%}
+{%- endif -%}
+{%- set _g4_has_off = '<|think_off|>' in ns_g4.sys_text -%}
+{%- set _g4_has_on = '<|think_on|>' in ns_g4.sys_text -%}
+{%- if _g4_has_off or _g4_has_on -%}
+    {%- if _g4_has_off and _g4_has_on -%}
+        {%- set enable_thinking = (ns_g4.sys_text.split('<|think_off|>')|last|length) > (ns_g4.sys_text.split('<|think_on|>')|last|length) -%}
+    {%- else -%}
+        {%- set enable_thinking = _g4_has_on -%}
+    {%- endif -%}
+{%- endif -%}
 {{- bos_token -}}
 {#- Handle System/Tool Definitions Block -#}
 {%- if enable_thinking or tools or (messages and messages[0]['role'] in ['system', 'developer']) -%}
@@ -196,10 +225,11 @@
     {%- endif -%}
     {%- if messages and messages[0]['role'] in ['system', 'developer'] -%}
         {%- if messages[0]['content'] is string -%}
-            {{- messages[0]['content'] | trim -}}
+            {{- (messages[0]['content'].split('<|think_off|>')|join('')).split('<|think_on|>')|join('') | trim -}}
         {%- elif messages[0]['content'] is iterable and messages[0]['content'] is not string and messages[0]['content'] is not mapping -%}
             {%- for item in messages[0]['content'] -%}
-                {{- item['text'] | trim + ' '-}}
+                {%- set _g4t = (item.get('text') or '') -%}
+                {{- (_g4t.split('<|think_off|>')|join('')).split('<|think_on|>')|join('') | trim + ' '-}}
             {%- endfor -%}
         {%- endif -%}
         {%- set loop_messages = messages[1:] -%}
